-- India’s Gujarat Targets 20% of Power From Renewables by 2020
-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 2012-04-20T04:58:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/india-s-gujarat-targets-20-of-power-from-renewables-by-2020.html
India ’s western state of Gujarat
plans to generate 20 percent of its electricity from clean
sources by 2020, Principal Secretary of Energy D.J. Pandian said
at a conference in Gandhinagar today.  That will require building at least 10,000 megawatts of
solar, wind and other renewable power plants, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
